      "description": "The life of Lillian Roth, a successful Broadway singer in the 1930s, her problems with various husbands, and the account of her alcoholism - portrayed in detail and with chilling clarity.   Based on the artist's confessional book, this film biography is authentic, harrowing thanks to Susan Hayward's credible performance, and a powerful warning against all forms of addiction. .",
